Merge pull request #31 from mehmetg/sauceondemandlistener-refactor Refactored SauceOnDemandListener and a minor test update.
Ran lint, optimized imports and removed one unused assignment.

Refactored the sauce test class to a base and subclass with test content. Reused sauce base test class to run session id and job-name printing test and checking output by capturing stdout. The nature of the feature being tested forced some unorthodox testing. Also removed build id update from the SauceOnDemandTestListener class to give user the freedom to set their own. In the earlier setup the Jenkins tag was overwriting the user set one causing odd behaviour.

Refactored SauceOnDemandListener to print out the session id at the end of the test. It was trying to print it before the session was generated. Merged and cleaned up helper methods a bit.

Removed SauceOnDemandSessionIdProvider member variable as it was not threadsafe. It likely
was causing the sporadic errors observed on highly concurrent test sessions.

Unit tests are passing.
